comments:
Abolished 1.4.1939 and divided between the parishes of Garforth 
    and Castleford. See also Table 2, notes (k) and (x).

That part which until 1.4.1938 formed part of the parish of 
    Allerton Bywater. See also Table 2, note (x).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of South Milford, 
    Monk Fryston and Huddleston with Newthorpe. See also Table 2, notes (d), (n) 
    and (x).

Created 1.4.1937 out of the parishes of Newthorpe and Huddleston 
    cum Lumby. See also Table 2, note (w).

Abolished 1.4.1939 and added to the parish of Garforth. See 
    also Table 2, note (k).

That part which until 9.11.1912 formed part of the parish of Barwick in Elmet. 
    See also Table 2, note (p).

That part which until 1.4.1937 formed parts of the part of the parish of Austhorpe, 
    Barwick in Elmet and Swillington. See also Table 2, note (u).

That part which until 1.4.1937 formed part of the parish of 
    Huddleston cum Lumby. See also Table 2, note (x).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Huddleston 
    with Newthorpe. See also Table 2, note (d).
